Hawks members reacted on information that a truck and a pilot vehicle travelling along the R45 was transporting drugs. CAPE TOWN Mandrax tablets worth R7.5 million were confiscated during a Hawks operation outside Vredenburg on Monday night. Four suspects from Gauteng were arrested and are expected to make an appearance in the Vredenburg Magistrates Court on Wednesday. Hawks Western Cape spokesperson Lloyd Ramovha says members reacted on information that a truck and a pilot vehicle travelling along the R45 was allegedly transporting and escorting drugs. The illegal trade of drugs has been dealt a severe blow after an intelligence-led operation led by members of the Hawks, the South African Narcotics Enforcement Bureau swept on four drug dealers aged between 31 and 58. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)